That part which until 1.4.1932 formed the parishes of Lee on 
    the Solent and Rowner. See also Table 2, note (g).
See Table 2, note (f).

Created 1894 from the parishes of Widley and Wymering. Renamed 
    13.10.1921 to become the parish of Widley. See also Table 2, notes (d) and (e).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Titchfield. Abolished 1.4.1932 
    and added to the parish of Fareham.

Created 1.4.1932 from the parishes of Titchfield and Sarisbury. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
See Table 2, note (g).

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Southwick and Widley. See also Table 2, note (g).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Titchfield. Abolished 1.4.1932 
    and added to the parish of Fareham.

Created 1.4.1930 out of the parishes of Crofton and Rowner. Abolished 
    1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Alverstoke. See also Table 2, note 
    (g).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Fareham 
    and Portsmouth. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 9.11.1904 formed part of the parish of 
    Cosham. See also Table 2, note (d).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Alverstoke. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a), (b) and (g).

Created 30.9.1894 out of the parish of Titchfield. Abolished 1.4.1932 
    and divided between the parishes of Fareham and Curbridge.

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Wickham. See also Table 2, note (f).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Southwick

Created 1.4.1932 out of the parishes of Southwick, Widley, Waterloo and Farlington. See also Table 2, note (f).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Fareham 
    and Curbridge.
See Table 2, notes (f) and (f).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Cosham.

Created 13.10.1921 by renaming the parish of Widley. Abolished

Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Cosham.
